    {
      "id": "Oz-bAiT0jE_x-305hDdK4",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 3695.793224868453,
      "y": 624.7208850486613,
      "width": 1291.1390380859375,
      "height": 1075,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffc9c9",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b1DG",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1244424568,
      "version": 2683,
      "versionNonce": 1953648008,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1775502946329,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "RULES:\n\nTemplate\nAccount Number: get from Billing Account Number section in the course dog\n\nReservation Number: MMDDVENUE_CODEAM/PM (Venue codes are retrived from the @Venue_Code_for_Resevation_number.txt)\n(if the event is in the AM use AM else PM)\n\nVENUE: (by default use the location name in the coursedog but for edge case use Venue_Code_for_Venue_dictionary dictionary)\n\nSETUP_INSTRUCTION (Already present in the internal events notes if not contact superisor)\n\nSetup time:\n *By default 2 hrs before the event\n\nEdge Cases:\n1. there should be no setup time between 12-1 pm (lunch break)\n\n2. Facilities work hours: 8:00 AM - 5:00 PM so if the event is early of eg: 8 AM then setup at 6 AM Max but if\nthe event has minimal setup like 1 table with 2 chairs then put setup time as 1 hour before the event\n\n3. setup time should not overlap between any other event happening in that venue (also consider events which has no setup)\n\n4. if there is an event before this and there is no time for setup that is less then 60 min notify manager, and if there is 1 hour for\nthe setup use SHARP an the end of the setup time eg: 9 AM SHARP\n\n5. If the event is after 5 PM and there is no event happening at that venue then put setup time at 11 AM\n\n6. If the same event ID spans multiple consecutive calendar days, generate ONE internal event note. The reservation number uses\nthe first day's date (MMDD). Setup time is before the first day; breakdown is after the last day.\n\n7. If 2 hours before the event start would land before 8 AM (e.g., event starts at 9 AM), set setup time to the previous day at 4\nPM instead of capping at 6 AM, only if there is no event in that venue after 4 PM. (Exception: it costs more on the weekends to\nhost an event, as facilities charge extra on weekends, so if the event is on Monday morning, put the setup time 2 hrs before the\nevent time)\n\nBreakdown time\n *By default its ncxt day in the AM\nEdge Cases:\n1. if there is an event happening after this which has event setup in the same venue then put the breakdown in the PM\n \n2.  if the event is indoor and it on the weekend and there is no event in that space after it on the weekends the put breakdown\non Monday in the AM",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "center",
      "verticalAlign": "middle",
      "containerId": "heIUXKso-pp7WqL5i7Iro",
      "originalText": "RULES:\n\nTemplate\nAccount Number: get from Billing Account Number section in the course dog\n\nReservation Number: MMDDVENUE_CODEAM/PM (Venue codes are retrived from the @Venue_Code_for_Resevation_number.txt)\n(if the event is in the AM use AM else PM)\n\nVENUE: (by default use the location name in the coursedog but for edge case use Venue_Code_for_Venue_dictionary dictionary)\n\nSETUP_INSTRUCTION (Already present in the internal events notes if not contact superisor)\n\nSetup time:\n *By default 2 hrs before the event\n\nEdge Cases:\n1. there should be no setup time between 12-1 pm (lunch break)\n\n2. Facilities work hours: 8:00 AM - 5:00 PM so if the event is early of eg: 8 AM then setup at 6 AM Max but if\nthe event has minimal setup like 1 table with 2 chairs then put setup time as 1 hour before the event\n\n3. setup time should not overlap between any other event happening in that venue (also consider events which has no setup)\n\n4. if there is an event before this and there is no time for setup that is less then 60 min notify manager, and if there is 1 hour for the setup use SHARP an the end of the setup time eg: 9 AM SHARP\n\n5. If the event is after 5 PM and there is no event happening at that venue then put setup time at 11 AM\n\n6. If the same event ID spans multiple consecutive calendar days, generate ONE internal event note. The reservation number uses the first day's date (MMDD). Setup time is before the first day; breakdown is after the last day.\n\n7. If 2 hours before the event start would land before 8 AM (e.g., event starts at 9 AM), set setup time to the previous day at 4 PM instead of capping at 6 AM, only if there is no event in that venue after 4 PM. (Exception: it costs more on the weekends to host an event, as facilities charge extra on weekends, so if the event is on Monday morning, put the setup time 2 hrs before the event time)\n\nBreakdown time\n *By default its ncxt day in the AM\nEdge Cases:\n1. if there is an event happening after this which has event setup in the same venue then put the breakdown in the PM\n \n2.  if the event is indoor and it on the weekend and there is no event in that space after it on the weekends the put breakdown on Monday in the AM",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
